1.9.4 PEP 366: Explicit Relative Imports From a Main Module
-----------------------------------------------------------

Python’s *note -m: 8b4. switch allows running a module as a script.
When you ran a module that was located inside a package, relative
imports didn’t work correctly.

The fix for Python 2.6 adds a *note __package__: 56b. attribute to
modules.  When this attribute is present, relative imports will be
relative to the value of this attribute instead of the *note __name__:
8d3. attribute.

PEP 302-style importers can then set *note __package__: 56b. as
necessary.  The *note runpy: e0. module that implements the *note -m:
8b4. switch now does this, so relative imports will now work correctly
in scripts running from inside a package.


