1.10.5 PEP 338: Executing Modules as Scripts
--------------------------------------------

The *note -m: 8b4. switch added in Python 2.4 to execute a module as a
script gained a few more abilities.  Instead of being implemented in C
code inside the Python interpreter, the switch now uses an
implementation in a new module, *note runpy: e0.

The *note runpy: e0. module implements a more sophisticated import
mechanism so that it’s now possible to run modules in a package such as
‘pychecker.checker’.  The module also supports alternative import
mechanisms such as the *note zipimport: 140. module.  This means you can
add a .zip archive’s path to ‘sys.path’ and then use the *note -m: 8b4.
switch to execute code from the archive.

